8.11 SQL Authentication Testing
8.11.1 Security Implementation
Password Security
The system implements industry-standard password security using SHA2_512 hashing combined with unique salts for each user. This approach ensures that even if the database is compromised, passwords cannot be reversed or used in rainbow table attacks.
Session Management
User sessions are managed through cryptographically secure tokens with automatic 24-hour expiry. The sp_ValidateSession procedure ensures all protected endpoints verify session validity before allowing access.
Brute Force Protection
The system protects against brute force attacks by implementing a failed login attempt counter. After 5 failed attempts within 15 minutes, the account is temporarily locked, preventing automated password guessing.
Audit Trail
All authentication events are logged in the AuditLog table, providing a complete history of user activity for security monitoring and compliance.

